description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/router.c
Lines: 359-376

In lichen_router_clear_pending():

    int cleared = 0;
    for (size_t i = 0; i < CONFIG_LICHEN_ROUTER_MAX_PENDING; i++) {
        struct lichen_pending_packet *p = &router->pending[i];
        if (p->valid && memcmp(p->destination_iid, dst_iid, 8) == 0) {
            p->valid = false;
            cleared++;
        }
    }
    router->pending_count -= (size_t)cleared;

If pending_count gets out of sync (e.g., due to a bug elsewhere), and cleared > pending_count, the subtraction will underflow since pending_count is size_t (unsigned).

Same issue in lichen_router_expire_pending (line 396):
    router->pending_count -= (size_t)expired;

And in lichen_gradient_remove_via (gradient.c line 211):
    table->count -= (size_t)removed;

Consider adding defensive checks: 
    if ((size_t)cleared <= router->pending_count) {
        router->pending_count -= (size_t)cleared;
    } else {
        router->pending_count = 0;  // Reset on inconsistency
    }
